<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,1353,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,392,1353,1379]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown, pronotum, and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[807,874,1353,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[861,874,1353,1379]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black, with pair of lateral white maculae on pronotal disc. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[833,903,1393,1419]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[888,903,1393,1419]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark red with three elongate transverse white maculae. Paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[661,731,1433,1459]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[716,731,1433,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) branched, asymmetrical, with left branch located ventrally, shorter and curved; right branch located dorsally, distinctly longer, and with apex curved ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,1353,1899]" box="[312,669,1553,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,408,1553,1579]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Length.</emphasis>
Male, 13.0– 
<quantity box="[557,665,1553,1579]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.39" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="13.9">13.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,1353,1899]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1323,284,350]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,543,1593,1619]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[640,714,1593,1619]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[701,714,1593,1619]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) with median length of crown about four­tenths interocular width and one­fourth transocular width; ocelli located on pair of coronal foveae and closer to inner eye margin than to median line of head; epistomal suture (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,279,1713,1739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) complete; clypeus not produced, with upper portion continuing contour of frons in profile, lower portion more nearly horizontal than remainder of face. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1251,1753,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[1238,1251,1753,1779]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) with width approximately equal to transocular width; disc transversely striated and glabrous; posterior margin almost rectilinear; dorsopleural carinae complete, declivous anteriorly. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[406,477,1873,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 
<number box="[462,477,1873,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distinct veins, opaque, without punctures; membrane not clearly delimited. Hindfemoral setal formula 
<number box="[718,740,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<number box="[746,760,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[765,779,284,310]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1.0">1</number>
. Other morphological characters of head and thorax as in the generic description (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[737,884,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2, New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977">
Young 
<number box="[821,884,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[895,944,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="669.0">669</number>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" targetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1322,1749,1887]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,435,1749,1773]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIGURES 1–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[442,669,1750,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talitae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[442,669,1750,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Scoposcartula talitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[676,758,1750,1773]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,283,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,502,283,309]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[627,703,284,310]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[686,703,284,310]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, subtriangular with apex truncate; macrosetae on posterior portion, extending anteriorly along ventral margin. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[352,426,363,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[411,426,363,389]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) triangular, tapered towards apex, with few macrosetae near apex. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[273,348,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[331,348,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending approximately as far posteriorly as connective apex; apical portion curved, digitiform, directed outwards. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1123,443,469]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1106,1123,443,469]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T­shaped; arms short; stem long and thin, narrowed towards apex. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1179,1249,482,508]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1234,1249,482,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) symmetrical, without basiventral process; shaft, in lateral view, with two tiny dentiform processes on dorsal margin. Paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[726,801,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[786,801,562,588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, branched, with left branch located ventrally, shorter and curved; right branch located dorsally, distinctly longer, and with apex curved ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,283,1899]" box="[312,535,681,707]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,535,681,707]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Female unknown.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,283,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,388,720,746]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Color.</emphasis>
Head, pronotum, and scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[777,844,721,747]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[831,844,721,747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark brown to black; forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1313,721,747]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1298,1313,721,747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) and abdomen red. Face (
<figureCitation box="[558,630,761,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[615,630,761,787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with white elongate macula on central portion extending from margin of crown to mid­length of frons; two white maculae including lateral margins of frons and part of genae and lora; rostrum brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[997,1065,840,866]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1052,1065,840,866]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) with two white maculae on lateral portions extending to lateral lobes. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1005,1077,880,906]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1062,1077,880,906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) dark red with three white elongate transverse maculae: basal one on corium and clavus, extending from costal portion to anal portion, median one mostly on corium, extending from costal portion over discal and brachial cells and reaching distal half of clavus, distal one on corium mostly across anteapical cells; apical margin of forewings with dark brown area including second to fifth apical cells and part of first apical and anteapical cells. First and second pairs of legs mostly brown up to apex of femora, tibiae and tarsi dark brown; third pair of legs mostly red up to apex of femora; tibiae and tarsi brown to dark brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
