<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,283,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,528,1476,1502]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
The color pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[772,876,1476,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talitae">
<emphasis box="[772,876,1476,1501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. talitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very different from that of the other species in the genus, so that the new taxon can be easily recognized by external examination only. The new species shares with 
<taxonomicName box="[725,833,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perrisi">
<emphasis box="[725,833,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. perrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[848,968,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limitata">
<emphasis box="[848,968,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. limitata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[983,1137,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inspergata">
<emphasis box="[983,1137,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. inspergata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1152,1315,1556,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovittata">
<emphasis box="[1152,1315,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flavovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[315,425,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tobiasi">
<emphasis box="[315,425,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. tobiasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the presence of an asymmetrical paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[962,1032,1595,1621]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[1017,1032,1595,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) with a branch, process, or projection. However, among these, it shares only with 
<taxonomicName box="[946,1054,1635,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perrisi">
<emphasis box="[946,1054,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. perrisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1278,1635,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovittata">
<emphasis box="[1114,1278,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flavovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the absence of a basiventral process on the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[859,932,1674,1700]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[915,932,1674,1700]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). The pygofers of 
<taxonomicName box="[1153,1258,1675,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talitae">
<emphasis box="[1153,1258,1675,1700]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. talitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,280,1714,1740]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[348,511,1715,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovitatta">
<emphasis box="[348,511,1715,1740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flavovitatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also similar, particularly because of the truncate apex. The male genitalia of these two species differ mostly in the relative size and shape of the branches of the paraphysis (
<figureCitation box="[447,518,1794,1820]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[264,383,1749,1773]" captionTargetBox="[303,1281,422,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[271,1317,414,1743]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Scoposcartula talitae sp. nov. (1) Crown, pronotum and scutellum; (2) face (antennae not entirely illustrated); (3) right forewing; (4) male pygofer, lateral view; (5) valve and left subgenital plate, ventral view; (6) left style and connective, dorsal view; (7) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view; (8) paraphysis, lateral view. Figure 3 from male paratype, others from male holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170730/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[502,518,1794,1820]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[572,676,1794,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talitae">
<emphasis box="[572,676,1794,1819]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. talitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the dorsal (right) branch is shorter and less curved than in 
<taxonomicName box="[297,462,1834,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scoposcartula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovittata">
<emphasis box="[297,462,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. flavovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the ventral (left) branch is longer and curved, whereas in the latter species it is straight.
</paragraph>
